@vyommani  - good point. This regression is caused by one of my commits - https://github.com/apache/ranger/pull/487/commits/4a0e5bb6da3060be5a8e1f1f8275f3b4b4fb245c#diff-cc35b70f378515ceb3c6393826e71032a9d795d3d2623acae413790a6ce6cb54R477. I will review further for such issues shortly.

> The code changes look good to me. However, I do have a question: were the changes made manually, or did you update the code style plugin to use the diamond operator (<>) and perform null checks manually?

IDE (IntellJ) flags potential NPE warnings, and suggests using <> operator while instantiating generic types. Tjese changes will need to be made manually though.

@developster such type of fix is not required, as only Ranger application is executed from Ranger Embedded Tomcat and Ranger server uses dedicated port to run.

This will force every user to change their Ranger Admin urls getting used for communicating to Ranger Rest APIs.

However this fix is breaking Ranger Admin url while accessing it with Knox gateway.

cc @pradeepagrawal8184 / @mneethiraj / @kumaab
